df":2.386294361119891},"entity":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.386294361119891},"separate":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.386294361119891},"mapping":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.386294361119891}},"documents":{"ep_stage_diary_001":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260417-202804","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_001","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Add a comment whenever a role is intentionally excluded from an access check — it makes the design rationale explicit and saves future readers from questioning the exclusion.\",\"scope\":\"auth/Payload access control\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"AdvancedContentEditor is the exercise-editor role (manages exercises) and is distinct from course-manager roles — they should not have course-level read access by design.\",\"scope\":\"LMS role model\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T20:39:05.717Z","wordCount":498,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,61,69,80,88,102,119,126,137,147,154,164,177,183,190,203,219,232,240,245,253,260,272,279,292,299,328,337,344,350,358,376,390,397,405,425,434,441,447,452,462,472,480,484,489]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260417-202804","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Adding a clarifying comment is a valid fix when the behavior is correct by design but not self-explanatory to future readers.\",\"scope\":\"code review\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"AdvancedContentEditor is an exercise-editor role, not a course-manager role — intentionally excluded from instructor list read access.\",\"scope\":\"LMS/permissions\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When fixing review feedback, prefer the minimal appropriate solution rather than over-engineering.\",\"scope\":\"PR workflow\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T21:21:41.525Z","wordCount":548,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,54,61,70,81,94,100,113,125,136,147,151,156,171,178,189,197,202,213,220,229,236,264,273,280,286,292,299,307,314,328,342,353,358,363,373,381,385,401,408,417,429,436,443,453,464,472,484,493,500,505,510,525,533,536]},"ep_stage_diary_003":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-070628","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_003","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Code with surprising exclusions (like AdvancedContentEditor from read access) should include a clarifying comment at the exclusion site explaining the design rationale, not just the intent.\",\"scope\":\"auth\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Multi-pass structured review (CRI-Triage → CRI-Detail → CRII-Context → CRIII-Holistic) catches both correctness issues and design-rationale gaps that single-pass reviews miss.\",\"scope\":\"code-review\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Without an inline comment at the exclusion site itself, reviewers cannot distinguish intentional design from accidental omission — always comment the 'why' at the decision point.\",\"scope\":\"auth\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T07:33:14.490Z","wordCount":713,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,52,59,69,80,92,97,124,129,144,154,165,180,190,195,210,217,228,232,241,251,259,268,275,284,291,297,302,313,321,325,334,338,347,352,362,368,378,386,391,403,414,421,431,441,448,453,461,469,477,482,493,500,509,516,527,534,549,559,564,572,582,589,601,613,625,636,647,654,679,688,697,705]},"ep_review_001":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-070628","episodeId":"ep_review_001","source":"review","content":"I now have a complete picture of the PR. Here is the structured review.\n\n---\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Summary\n\nPR #1266 implements the Instructor role and per-course permissions for the LMS. The primary change is a clarifying comment in `CourseInstructors.ts` (lines 98–99) explaining why `AdvancedContentEditor` is intentionally excluded from read access — resolving the sole open item from the previous Kody review. Supporting infrastructure includes the `CourseInstructors` collection, `instructorAccess.ts` helpers, and the `/api/instructor/gradebook/[courseId]` endpoint.\n\n## Findings\n\n### Critical\nNone.\n\n### Major\nNone.\n\n### Minor\nNone — the previously flagged minor item (missing design-rationale comment) is now resolved at `CourseInstructors.ts:98–99`.\n\n---\n\n## Two-Pass Review\n\n**Pass 1 — CRITICAL:**\n\n### SQL & Data Safety\nAll queries use Payload's parameterized `where` clauses (`equals`, `in` operators). No string interpolation in queries. The gradebook route uses `enrolledUsers.docs.map","createdAt":"2026-04-18T07:33:14.509Z","wordCount":1000,"positions":[2,13,22,37,41,53,64,81,90,99,108,112,117,132,143,152,156,163,183,192,200,212,223,235,253,258,264,267,271,287,313,327,341,346,355,369,374,379,393,402,407,415,426,441,455,474,487,504,508,527,531,542,553,564,578,592,601,612,618,629,635,646,657,665,671,677,685,692,702,714,718,731,749,752,755,769,773,778,788,797,814,820,825,836,844,848,858,880,890,904,916,919,926,943,956,966,972,978,992,997]},"ep_stage_diary_004":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-070628","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_004","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Document intentional security exclusions in comments near the exclusion logic, explaining why access is denied rather than granted — this resolves ambiguity during review.\",\"scope\":\"src/payload/collections/CourseInstructors.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"LMS access control uses a dedicated helper file (instructorAccess.ts) rather than inlining permissions, keeping collection configs clean and reusable.\",\"scope\":\"src/payload/access/instructorAccess.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"AdvancedContentEditor must be explicitly excluded from read access in instructor permissions; omitting this exclusion silently grants broader read access than intended.\",\"scope\":\"LMS instructor permissions\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T07:35:53.655Z","wordCount":753,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,59,68,80,89,103,112,121,131,138,153,163,170,177,182,197,206,216,223,233,241,245,253,265,283,290,297,310,317,321,328,336,343,353,360,366,383,387,394,399,408,421,429,440,448,458,470,478,482,490,497,514,521,528,537,544,566,574,585,599,604,614,625,638,652,662,671,678,686,691,698,703,715,723,727,738]},"ep_stage_diary_005":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-093152","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_005","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Admin/superuser views often get stubbed with TODO initially — always verify the admin branch returns data, not just instructor views.\",\"scope\":\"UI branching\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Design token warnings in lint are acceptable in this project (not blocking) — only actual errors fail the gate.\",\"scope\":\"lint\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"When roles share a route, branch on role at both API (data) and UI (view) layers to keep concerns separated.\",\"scope\":\"auth routing\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Use Payload's `where` clause operators (equals, in) for parameterized queries — never string interpolation.\",\"scope\":\"payload api\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T09:44:07.292Z","wordCount":695,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,61,71,77,83,87,100,105,117,124,135,141,148,156,162,166,171,182,191,199,202,216,223,236,243,250,256,268,277,296,305,309,321,326,333,340,349,357,365,374,381,392,404,410,418,425,435,443,448,453,463,467,473,483,488,497,510,518,523,535,542,555,562,566,584,591,602,618,632,642,648,655,672,680,688]},"ep_stage_diary_006":{"taskId":"fix-pr-1266-260418-093152","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_006","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Translations must update both messages/en.json and messages/he.json whenever new UI text is added.\",\"scope\":\"i18n\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"API endpoints branch on isAdmin/role to return filtered (user-scoped) vs. unfiltered (admin) datasets.\",\"scope\":\"API design\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Admin dashboard uses courses[].instructors[] array on course entity rather than separate instructor->courses mapping.\",\"scope\":\"data model\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T09:47:48.706Z","wordCount":503,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,56,63,76,81,88,93,102,105,114,123,126,131,140,144,147,155,164,172,181,188,201,208,212,222,232,240,248,255,265,270,278,282,294,301,313,321,325,336,343,354,361,367,377,382,392,406,415,422,429,436,441,450,462,470,481,489,494]}},"totalDocs":7}